  "texts": [
    "The DSA should clarify and reinforce risk assessment and mitigation requirements imposed on VLOPs concerning these aspects, as outlined in Articles 34 and 35.",
    "Ethical and philosophical critiqueAs highlighted during the analysis of regulatory antecedents, prior self-governance centered authority within commercial entities rather than democratically accountable institutions and citizens, raising legitimacy concerns [109].",
    "For instance, the ECD's intermediary liability approach granted platforms control over speech removal while limiting avenues for public participation in content governance.",
    "The ethical critique explores more abstract yet fundamental tensions between privatized speech regulation and participatory self-determination perpetuated under the DSA, alongside duties around truth and transparency.Private Governance and Participation Delegating speech regulation to private platforms (Code: NTD) conflicts with commitments to participatory self-governance, instead expanding corporate control over discourse aligned with private interests rather than civic oversight [8,17,29,135].",
    "This questions the legitimacy of privatized judgments over truth and risks disregarding expressive diversity."
